# Oakwood Golf Club — environment variables
#
# Copy to .env.local for local development (NOT committed — see .gitignore).
# Set in Vercel project settings for preview + production deployments.
#
# IMPORTANT: SMTP_PASSWORD is a secret. Never commit it, never log it,
# never paste it into chat / tickets / screenshots. Rotate if exposed.

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IONOS SMTP — used by all three form Server Actions (Kontakt, Signup, Renewal)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Host + port: IONOS accepts STARTTLS on 587 (recommended) or implicit TLS on 465.
SMTP_HOST=smtp.ionos.de
SMTP_PORT=587

# SMTP auth: the mailbox user and its password.
# For oakwoodgolfclub.de, this is typically the info@ mailbox.
SMTP_USER=info@oakwoodgolfclub.de
SMTP_PASSWORD=

# From: the address form emails appear to come from.
# Should match an existing mailbox on the SMTP_USER's domain so DKIM/SPF align.
SMTP_FROM=info@oakwoodgolfclub.de

# To: the inbox that receives form submissions.
# Can equal SMTP_FROM — by default form emails go into the info@ inbox.
SMTP_TO=info@oakwoodgolfclub.de

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Turnstile — Spam-Schutz auf allen drei Formularen
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Kostenlos + unbegrenzt, DSGVO-konform (kein Cookie, kein Cross-Site-Tracking).
# Account: https://dash.cloudflare.com → Turnstile → Add Site → Widget anlegen.
# Liefert Sitekey (public, beginnt mit `0x...`) + Secret Key.
#
# Feature-Flags — BEIDE müssen "true" sein, damit der Captcha greift:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_CAPTCHA_ENABLED  (client — rendert das Widget)
#   CAPTCHA_ENABLED              (server — erzwingt die Verifikation, in
#                                 Production fail-closed, wenn Secret fehlt)
# Default leer/"false" = aus → Spam-Schutz kommt dann nur aus dem Rate-Limit.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CAPTCHA_ENABLED=
CAPTCHA_ENABLED=
#
# Public Sitekey — wird im Client-Bundle ausgeliefert, kein Geheimnis.
# Cloudflare-Test-Sitekey (always-pass, nur für lokale Entwicklung):
#   1x00000000000000000000AA
NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITEKEY=
#
# Secret — NIE commiten, NIE in den Client bundlen. In Vercel als "Sensitive"
# flaggen. Wird nur im Server Action für die siteverify-Prüfung verwendet.
# Cloudflare-Test-Secret (always-pass, nur für lokale Entwicklung):
#   1x0000000000000000000000000000000AA
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - If ANY of the SMTP_* vars above are missing, the form Server Actions fall
#   back to console-logging the composed email (server-side only) and still
#   return success to the user. This keeps local dev runnable without creds
#   and keeps preview deploys from eating a 500 if vars are mis-set.
# - To smoke-test SMTP from a Vercel preview, submit a Kontakt form and watch
#   the info@ inbox + the Vercel function logs for the request.
# - Friendly Captcha hat dieselbe Graceful-Degradation-Logik: ohne Sitekey
#   rendert das Client-Widget nichts; ohne API-Key überspringt der Server
#   die Verifikation. Damit bleibt die Form in Dev + Preview submit-fähig.
#   In Production MÜSSEN beide Vars gesetzt sein, sonst ist der Spam-Schutz
#   inaktiv (und es gibt eine Server-Console-Warnung).
